editorial:
**Idea — standard BFS**: Use a queue, push starting node 0, mark visited, then pop, append to output, and enqueue each unseen neighbour in the adjacency list's order.

```javascript
function bfsDeliveryHubs(graph) {
  const visited = new Set([0]);
  const queue = [0];
  const order = [];
  while (queue.length) {
    const u = queue.shift();
    order.push(u);
    for (const v of graph[u]) {
      if (!visited.has(v)) {
        visited.add(v);
        queue.push(v);
      }
    }
  }
  return order;
}
```

**Time**: O(V+E). **Space**: O(V).

Deterministic order milta hai kyunki adjacency list me neighbours sorted/given order me hain — usi order me enqueue karte hain.

