editorial:
**Idea — iterative DFS using stack**: Push start, then pop loop. To preserve left-to-right neighbour order in pre-order output, push neighbours in **reverse** order so the first neighbour ends up on top.

```javascript
function dfsMerchantNetwork(graph, start) {
  const visited = new Set();
  const stack = [start];
  const order = [];
  while (stack.length) {
    const u = stack.pop();
    if (visited.has(u)) continue;
    visited.add(u);
    order.push(u);
    for (let i = graph[u].length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
      if (!visited.has(graph[u][i])) stack.push(graph[u][i]);
    }
  }
  return order;
}
```

**Time**: O(V+E). **Space**: O(V).

Visit-on-pop pattern duplicate stack entries handle kar leta hai — push pe check zaruri nahi.

