**Idea — DFS sweep**: Build the adjacency list. Iterate every vertex; if not yet visited, fire a DFS to flood-fill its component and increment a counter.

```javascript
function countRailwayComponents(n, edges) {
  const adj = Array.from({length: n}, () => []);
  for (const [u, v] of edges) {
    adj[u].push(v);
    adj[v].push(u);
  }
  const visited = new Array(n).fill(false);
  let comps = 0;
  for (let start = 0; start < n; start++) {
    if (visited[start]) continue;
    comps++;
    const stack = [start];
    visited[start] = true;
    while (stack.length) {
      const u = stack.pop();
      for (const v of adj[u]) if (!visited[v]) { visited[v] = true; stack.push(v); }
    }
  }
  return comps;
}
```

**Time**: O(V+E). **Space**: O(V+E). Union-Find bhi same answer dega.

