editorial:
**Idea — Union-Find**: For each edge `(u,v)`, find roots. If equal, adding this edge would close a cycle → return true. Else union and continue.

```javascript
function hasWarehouseCycle(n, edges) {
  const parent = Array.from({length: n}, (_, i) => i);
  function find(x) { while (parent[x] !== x) { parent[x] = parent[parent[x]]; x = parent[x]; } return x; }
  for (const [u, v] of edges) {
    const ru = find(u), rv = find(v);
    if (ru === rv) return true;
    parent[ru] = rv;
  }
  return false;
}
```

**Time**: ~O((V+E) α(V)). **Space**: O(V).

DFS variant: track visited; from `u` recurse into neighbours `v ≠ parent`. Visiting an already-visited non-parent → cycle.

