editorial:
**Idea — BFS distance**: BFS from source; the layer at which `target` is dequeued is its distance. Maintain `dist[]` initialised to -1, push source with `dist[source] = 0`.

```javascript
function shortestStops(graph, source, target) {
  if (source === target) return 0;
  const n = graph.length;
  const dist = new Array(n).fill(-1);
  dist[source] = 0;
  const queue = [source];
  while (queue.length) {
    const u = queue.shift();
    for (const v of graph[u]) {
      if (dist[v] === -1) {
        dist[v] = dist[u] + 1;
        if (v === target) return dist[v];
        queue.push(v);
      }
    }
  }
  return -1;
}
```

**Time**: O(V+E). **Space**: O(V).

