editorial:
**Idea — flood fill on land cells**: Iterate every cell; on a `1` not yet sunk, increment counter and DFS/BFS to mark every connected land as visited (or overwrite to `0`).

```javascript
function numberOfIslands(grid) {
  const rows = grid.length, cols = grid[0].length;
  const visited = Array.from({length: rows}, () => new Array(cols).fill(false));
  const dirs = [[1,0],[-1,0],[0,1],[0,-1]];
  let count = 0;
  for (let r = 0; r < rows; r++) {
    for (let c = 0; c < cols; c++) {
      if (grid[r][c] !== 1 || visited[r][c]) continue;
      count++;
      const stack = [[r, c]];
      visited[r][c] = true;
      while (stack.length) {
        const [x, y] = stack.pop();
        for (const [dx, dy] of dirs) {
          const nx = x + dx, ny = y + dy;
          if (nx>=0&&ny>=0&&nx<rows&&ny<cols&&grid[nx][ny]===1&&!visited[nx][ny]) {
            visited[nx][ny] = true;
            stack.push([nx, ny]);
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
  return count;
}
```

**Time**: O(R*C). **Space**: O(R*C) for visited.

