editorial:
**Idea — reverse-mark from borders**: Every 1 reachable from a border 1 is safe. Run DFS/BFS from every border-1 marking those as `2`. After scanning, convert remaining 1→0 (surrounded got flipped) and 2→1 (restore safe).

```javascript
function flipSurroundedRegions(board) {
  const R = board.length, C = board[0].length;
  const dirs = [[1,0],[-1,0],[0,1],[0,-1]];
  function dfs(r, c) {
    if (r<0||c<0||r>=R||c>=C||board[r][c]!==1) return;
    board[r][c] = 2;
    for (const [dx,dy] of dirs) dfs(r+dx, c+dy);
  }
  for (let r = 0; r < R; r++) { dfs(r, 0); dfs(r, C-1); }
  for (let c = 0; c < C; c++) { dfs(0, c); dfs(R-1, c); }
  for (let r = 0; r < R; r++) for (let c = 0; c < C; c++) {
    if (board[r][c] === 1) board[r][c] = 0;
    else if (board[r][c] === 2) board[r][c] = 1;
  }
  return board;
}
```

**Time**: O(R*C). **Space**: O(R*C) recursion worst case.

