editorial:
**Idea — Kahn's topological sort**: Build adjacency `b → a` and indegree of every course. Push degree-0 nodes. Pop one, decrement neighbours, push freshly-zero ones. Count processed; equal to numCourses ⇒ no cycle.

```javascript
function canFinishCourses(numCourses, prerequisites) {
  const adj = Array.from({length: numCourses}, () => []);
  const indeg = new Array(numCourses).fill(0);
  for (const [a, b] of prerequisites) { adj[b].push(a); indeg[a]++; }
  const queue = [];
  for (let i = 0; i < numCourses; i++) if (indeg[i] === 0) queue.push(i);
  let processed = 0, head = 0;
  while (head < queue.length) {
    const u = queue[head++];
    processed++;
    for (const v of adj[u]) if (--indeg[v] === 0) queue.push(v);
  }
  return processed === numCourses;
}
```

**Time**: O(V+E). **Space**: O(V+E).

