editorial:
**Idea — transitive closure (O(V^3))**: With ≤ 100 nodes, build a `reach[V][V]` boolean matrix using Floyd-Warshall: `reach[i][j] |= reach[i][k] && reach[k][j]`.

```javascript
function checkPrereqs(numCourses, prerequisites, queries) {
  const n = numCourses;
  const reach = Array.from({length: n}, () => new Array(n).fill(false));
  for (const [u, v] of prerequisites) reach[u][v] = true;
  for (let k = 0; k < n; k++) {
    for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) {
      if (!reach[i][k]) continue;
      for (let j = 0; j < n; j++) {
        if (reach[k][j]) reach[i][j] = true;
      }
    }
  }
  return queries.map(([a, b]) => reach[a][b]);
}
```

**Time**: O(V^3 + Q). **Space**: O(V^2).
